Obstructive sleep apnea consists in recurrent episodes of partial obstruction of 
the upper airways which can determine cessation of breathing during sleep 
causing intermittent hypoxia. The obstructive sleep disorders are encountered 
predominantly in obese patients with or without metabolic syndrome, that can 
